],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"2CA249502E3C11EA895211B47B6D1758","steps":[{"id":866352,"guid":"7CE0F1502E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"97238D7282674A95887AE49FC216EB96","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Pre-treatment of sample"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C770905148D44693BD3684E44C0E855D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Cut sample into small slivers to a final weight of 25g.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866353,"guid":"86730BE02E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866352,"previous_guid":"7CE0F1502E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"88DF26A6930E4D14A06E12636CA6FAC3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Pre-treatment of sample"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6315EC9A79EF48878140370FDD4C56EF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Dilute the 25g portion in 225ml of <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Buffered Peptone Water (BPW) broth <\/span><span>(1:10 dilution). <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866354,"guid":"8F1373702E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866353,"previous_guid":"86730BE02E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"193A86FBE48448FB919E176BD0EAB7E1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Pre-treatment of sample"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"03515BF3375B465C95E623472648E72F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Mix the sample using a stomacher for 30 seconds or pulse using a blender.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866356,"guid":"BB743AD02E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866354,"previous_guid":"8F1373702E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9D2303F98D954D3AACB92AFAAD7D2D3A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Pre-treatment of sample"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"41B665A23E7E4C058D003C5EF847C40A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Incubate the suspension at <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">37\u00b0C \u00b1 1\u00b0C <\/span><span>for <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">24 h \u00b1 1 h<\/span><span>.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866358,"guid":"DC0BBC502E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866356,"previous_guid":"BB743AD02E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A6E4D337E84146BF946EF22278CFED9F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Streak a SCAi medium agar plate"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6E15E948AB484F558FB4E1D34A3F8FE7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Following 24h incubation, using a <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">10\u03bcl loop<\/span><span>, streak for single colonies onto the surface of a\nsmall petri dish (90 mm) of SCAI medium and incubate at <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">44\u00b0C \u00b1 1\u00b0C <\/span><span>for <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">48h \u00b1 1 h.<\/span><span><\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Sometimes, typical colonies (yellow, moist, dome-shaped) can be recognized after 24h culture on plates, but 48 h is much better to discriminate <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella<\/span><span>-looking colonies from other ones (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli <\/span><span>colonies are typically white because they do not use inositol).   <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>It can happen that the medium, which should initially be blue, turns completely yellow, when there are many inositol-fermenting colonies (typically <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella<\/span><span>). In these cases, discriminating yellow colonies is less easy. Diluting before streaking could help in these cases. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866360,"guid":"6885A6502E4211EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866358,"previous_guid":"DC0BBC502E4111EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"85C9E1A1E3AC4895AE92815491DEC45A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Purification and identification of suspect Klebsiella colonies"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D0C8BDEA94F44D95999964AFEED976AD","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Typical <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella <\/span><span>spp. colonies are yellow on SCAI medium.   <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Select suspect <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella<\/span><span> colonies for subculture and bacterial identification. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Streak the selected colonies onto the surface of a non-selective agar medium (e.g., LB or TSA) in a manner which will allow isolated colonies to develop. Incubate plates at 37 \u00b0C \u00b1 1\u00b0C for 24 h \u00b1 1 h.   <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Note: If colonies are numerous and close to each other, re-isolate the colony on another SCAi agar plate to control for purity. Incubate for up to 48h.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866361,"guid":"EDB060E02E4211EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866360,"previous_guid":"6885A6502E4211EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"69252D208D5745E6A7C38D96DF8AD3B4","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Purification and identification of suspect Klebsiella colonies"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"60D7A7D55FF54609A76FD31C727AE22C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Determine species of purified suspect K. pneumoniae colonies using MALDI-TOF mass spectrometry and\/or species-specific PCR.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866362,"guid":"F7A18B602E4211EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866363,"previous_guid":"26ABEEF02E4311EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"532929FE54FE4BD78697401A5AF88318","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Storage of bacterial strains"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"51E07D65500343839541C603ED483FCF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Freeze strains confirmed as <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella pneumoniae <\/span><span>(or its related species, which also grow on SCAi) at -80\u00b0C using CryoBank tubes or equivalent (e.g. BHI + 15% glycerol medium).<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">If several morphotypes are available, you may want to store one colony per morphotype.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866363,"guid":"26ABEEF02E4311EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866361,"previous_guid":"EDB060E02E4211EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1A76AA54BAF447F3928300FF309831B3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Mixed-colony storage for future studies (additional)"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"954B17FFC9694B9A9C23E93810661350","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">If desired, after picking selected colonies, sweep the remaining SCAi plate content and freeze it at -80\u00b0C (e.g., for mixed colonies sequencing) using CryoBank tubes or equivalent (e.g., in house BHI + 15% glycerol medium).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[{"id":348952,"mol_weight":0,"name":"myo-inositol","linfor":"","url":"http:\/\/","sku":"I5125-50 g","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma Aldrich","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/sigmaaldrich.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":17},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":348953,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Simmons citrate","linfor":"","url":"http:\/\/","sku":"64834-500g","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"BioRad Sciences","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.bio-rad.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":272},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol is intended for isolation of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella<\/span><span> strains from different food sources. It is derived from the initial description of the SCAi medium (van Kregten E, Westerdaal, N. A. C., and Willers, J. M. N. New, simple medium for selective recovery of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella pneumoniae<\/span><span> and <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella oxytoca <\/span><span>from human feces. Journal of Clinical Microbiology. 1984;20:936-41) and its validation across a diversity of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella<\/span><span> strains (Passet V, Brisse S. 2015. Association of tellurite resistance with hypervirulent clonal groups of<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> Klebsiella pneumoniae<\/span><span>. J Clin Microbiol. 53(4):1380-2). <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The protocol entails enrichment using Buffered Peptone Water (BPW), and plating on SCAi (Simmons Citrate with Inositol) agar.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol was optimized by the MedVetKlebs consortium using chicken meat and salad samples. <\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1578324601}